34:46.000 --> 34:49.000
as an expression of its efficiency,

34:50.000 --> 34:56.000
increasing productivity becomes the main way to increase profits.

34:57.000 --> 35:00.000
If self-worth is definitely influenced by profit,

35:01.000 --> 35:03.000
in the sense that the lower the self-worth, the more profit,

35:04.000 --> 35:06.000
then the above three factors,

35:07.000 --> 35:12.000
such as the volume of the implementation of the structure and the price level,

35:13.000 --> 35:15.000
are not unambiguous.

35:16.000 --> 35:19.000
In this respect, the influence on profit is the most important.

35:20.000 --> 35:23.000
The thing is that it is necessary to take into account

35:24.000 --> 35:26.000
the elasticity of the product.

35:27.000 --> 35:30.000
This is the most important point that a businessman needs to know,

35:31.000 --> 35:35.000
in order to properly implement his product.

35:36.000 --> 35:39.000
Every product has elasticity.

35:39.000 --> 35:46.000
Elasticity is the reaction of the product to the change in price.

35:47.000 --> 35:53.000
How will the demand for a given product change with the change in price?

35:54.000 --> 35:58.000
Elasticity is generally determined by the ratio of the increase in demand to the increase in price.

35:59.000 --> 36:03.000
It is clear that if the price increases, the demand decreases.

36:04.000 --> 36:06.000
Elasticity is always negative.

36:06.000 --> 36:11.000
But the increase in price and the increase in demand

36:12.000 --> 36:16.000
can be in different quantities.

36:17.000 --> 36:20.000
The demand can decrease faster than the increase in price,

36:21.000 --> 36:24.000
it can decrease slower than the increase in price,

36:25.000 --> 36:30.000
or it can decrease to the same degree as the price changes.

36:31.000 --> 36:34.000
Three levels of elasticity are determined.

36:34.000 --> 36:37.000
They say that the demand for non-elastic products

36:38.000 --> 36:43.000
decreases extremely slowly compared to the change in price.

36:44.000 --> 36:50.000
The most non-elastic product is the salt from the kitchen.

36:51.000 --> 36:53.000
You come to a store and see how much salt is in the kitchen.

36:54.000 --> 36:56.000
You see that a kilogram of salt costs 13 rubles.

36:57.000 --> 37:00.000
Tell me, please, if there is salt for 14 rubles,

37:01.000 --> 37:03.000
will people buy it less or more?

37:04.000 --> 37:08.000
The price is the same, but 15 rubles is the same,

37:09.000 --> 37:11.000
and 20 rubles is the same.

37:12.000 --> 37:17.000
We see that salt, despite the increase in its price,

37:18.000 --> 37:20.000
the demand for it does not change.

37:21.000 --> 37:26.000
This means that salt is an absolutely non-elastic product.

37:27.000 --> 37:30.000
With the help of salt, you can get additional profit.

37:30.000 --> 37:33.000
It's not a coincidence that in the old days,

37:34.000 --> 37:37.000
Russia had a state monopoly on salt.

37:38.000 --> 37:41.000
And only the state had the right to sell salt.

37:42.000 --> 37:44.000
However, this led to excessive increases in the price of salt,

37:45.000 --> 37:48.000
and it caused salt riots, history remembers it.

37:49.000 --> 37:53.000
Nevertheless, salt is such a non-elastic product

37:54.000 --> 37:58.000
that it can bring very high income to those who make it.

37:58.000 --> 38:04.000
The reason is that salt is very much needed by people.

38:05.000 --> 38:07.000
It cannot be replaced by anything.

38:08.000 --> 38:11.000
Salt cannot be replaced with sugar, milk, bread.

38:12.000 --> 38:14.000
Salt cannot be replaced by anything.

38:15.000 --> 38:16.000
It is very much needed.

38:17.000 --> 38:18.000
It is needed in small quantities.

38:19.000 --> 38:24.000
Moreover, the price of salt is so low

38:24.000 --> 38:29.000
that people's purchasing power

38:30.000 --> 38:36.000
is so low that they are easily swayed by the price of salt.

38:37.000 --> 38:40.000
The other opposite is the case of elastic products,

38:41.000 --> 38:46.000
where the smallest change in price can cause a huge drop in demand.

38:48.000 --> 38:52.000
This happens with products that have a lot of substitutes.

38:52.000 --> 38:54.000
A typical example is clothes.

38:55.000 --> 38:57.000
Clothes have so many substitutes

38:58.000 --> 39:03.000
that the buyer is ready to switch to any other type of clothing

39:04.000 --> 39:08.000
if the one he planned to buy seems too expensive to him.

39:09.000 --> 39:13.000
Therefore, clothes have a very high elasticity.

39:14.000 --> 39:21.000
The smallest increase in price can cause a huge drop in demand

39:22.000 --> 39:24.000
for elastic products.

39:25.000 --> 39:29.000
There are products with so-called single elasticity,

39:30.000 --> 39:36.000
where the price and demand changes are very much in the quantitative sense.

39:37.000 --> 39:41.000
The higher the price, the lower the demand.

39:41.000 --> 39:45.000
As a result, neither increase nor decrease in price

39:46.000 --> 39:48.000
bring any additional profit.

39:49.000 --> 39:51.000
Knowing what product you are producing

39:52.000 --> 39:54.000
is the first task of a businessman.

39:55.000 --> 39:56.000
And that is why.

39:57.000 --> 40:00.000
The thing is that in order to get additional profit from the product,

40:01.000 --> 40:03.000
you need to pay attention to its elasticity.

40:04.000 --> 40:05.000
For non-elastic products,

40:06.000 --> 40:07.000
look at salt,

40:07.000 --> 40:08.000
for non-elastic products,

40:09.000 --> 40:10.000
look at salt.

40:11.000 --> 40:12.000
In order to get additional profit,

40:13.000 --> 40:14.000
you need to raise the price.

40:15.000 --> 40:16.000
The price increases,

40:17.000 --> 40:18.000
the cost remains the same,

40:19.000 --> 40:20.000
and the profit increases sharply.

40:21.000 --> 40:22.000
And for elastic products,

40:23.000 --> 40:24.000
in order to increase the profit,

40:25.000 --> 40:27.000
you need to lower the price.

40:28.000 --> 40:29.000
Pay attention,

40:30.000 --> 40:31.000
for non-elastic products,

40:32.000 --> 40:33.000
you need to raise the price,

40:34.000 --> 40:35.000
and for elastic products,

40:35.000 --> 40:37.000
you need to lower the price a little bit.

40:38.000 --> 40:40.000
And the demand for this product increases sharply.

40:41.000 --> 40:42.000
Where does it come from?

40:43.000 --> 40:44.000
It's the former buyers of other products

40:45.000 --> 40:47.000
who were ready to buy other products earlier.

40:48.000 --> 40:49.000
But since only your product became cheaper,

40:50.000 --> 40:51.000
and not other products,

40:52.000 --> 40:53.000
they instantly switched to your product.

40:54.000 --> 40:56.000
The demand has increased sharply.

40:57.000 --> 41:00.000
You can sell tens, hundreds, thousands of times more products,

41:01.000 --> 41:03.000
lowering the price by a penny.

41:03.000 --> 41:06.000
Your profit from a single product decreases,

41:07.000 --> 41:09.000
but the mass of profit you get

41:10.000 --> 41:11.000
increases sharply,

41:12.000 --> 41:15.000
because you manage to sell a huge amount of products.

41:16.000 --> 41:19.000
But this method of lowering the price for elastic products

41:20.000 --> 41:24.000
can be used only if you are able to provide

41:25.000 --> 41:29.000
a larger number of products for the market.

41:30.000 --> 41:32.000
If you have a production,

41:33.000 --> 41:35.000
and you can increase the production,

41:36.000 --> 41:37.000
for example, from one shift to two,

41:38.000 --> 41:39.000
from two to three,

41:40.000 --> 41:41.000
or you have unlimited supplies,

41:42.000 --> 41:44.000
and you can order more and more products,

41:45.000 --> 41:48.000
then you can safely go for a price reduction

41:49.000 --> 41:50.000
for elastic products,

41:51.000 --> 41:52.000
sell more products,

41:53.000 --> 41:54.000
and get more profit.

41:55.000 --> 41:56.000
This is a very important point.

41:57.000 --> 41:58.000
And every businessman,

41:59.000 --> 42:02.000
before using the price and production volume

42:03.000 --> 42:04.000
to regulate his profit,

42:05.000 --> 42:06.000
should first think about

42:07.000 --> 42:11.000
the elasticity of the product he sells.

42:12.000 --> 42:15.000
But elasticity not only depends on nature.

42:16.000 --> 42:18.000
Elasticity of the product depends on

42:19.000 --> 42:23.000
the environment of the product and other products.

42:24.000 --> 42:27.000
If there are no competitors,

42:28.000 --> 42:29.000
substitutes,

42:30.000 --> 42:32.000
then your product increases its non-elasticity.

42:33.000 --> 42:34.000
And the same clothes,

42:35.000 --> 42:37.000
which would seem to be the most elastic product,

42:38.000 --> 42:39.000
if for some reason

42:40.000 --> 42:42.000
all competitors disappear,

42:43.000 --> 42:44.000
and you become the only seller of clothes,

42:45.000 --> 42:46.000
your product becomes non-elastic.

42:47.000 --> 42:48.000
And vice versa.

42:49.000 --> 42:51.000
If there are more and more competitors,

42:52.000 --> 42:54.000
and these competitors themselves reduce the price,

42:55.000 --> 42:57.000
then your product becomes more and more elastic,

42:58.000 --> 42:59.000
and all buyers leave you.

43:00.000 --> 43:02.000
And you can no longer produce your products.

43:03.000 --> 43:05.000
Thus, the environment

43:06.000 --> 43:08.000
affects the elasticity of your product.

43:10.000 --> 43:11.000
Knowing this,

43:12.000 --> 43:13.000
a businessman takes care not only of

43:14.000 --> 43:16.000
selling less elastic products,

43:17.000 --> 43:20.000
but also of creating an environment

43:21.000 --> 43:25.000
where the elasticity of the product decreases.

43:26.000 --> 43:28.000
For example, in the trading network you can see

43:29.000 --> 43:30.000
products that are sold

43:30.000 --> 43:32.000
under the trademark of a given trading network.

43:33.000 --> 43:35.000
And under this pretext,

43:36.000 --> 43:39.000
the company limits the purchase

43:40.000 --> 43:42.000
of similar products from other manufacturers,

43:43.000 --> 43:45.000
and only sells its own products

43:46.000 --> 43:48.000
under the brand of its trading network.

43:49.000 --> 43:50.000
And thus, in the trading network,

43:51.000 --> 43:52.000
there is only one salt,

43:53.000 --> 43:54.000
one single sugar.

43:55.000 --> 43:56.000
In the eyes of the buyer,

43:57.000 --> 43:58.000
the competition disappears.

43:58.000 --> 44:00.000
The elasticity of this product increases.

44:01.000 --> 44:03.000
The higher the elasticity of this product,

44:04.000 --> 44:06.000
the more you can boldly increase the price of the business,

44:07.000 --> 44:08.000
and make additional profit

44:09.000 --> 44:11.000
when selling such a product.

44:12.000 --> 44:13.000
Thus, we see

44:14.000 --> 44:16.000
that the volume of implementation

44:17.000 --> 44:18.000
and the price level of the product

44:19.000 --> 44:21.000
do not necessarily affect the profit,

44:22.000 --> 44:24.000
but through the elasticity of this product.

44:25.000 --> 44:26.000
It is important to pay attention

44:26.000 --> 44:27.000
to the elasticity of the product

44:28.000 --> 44:31.000
and to manage it.

