then we will go to the same level

01:11:47.000 --> 01:11:48.000
as they did

01:11:49.000 --> 01:11:50.000
in the scientific and technical progress.

01:11:51.000 --> 01:11:52.000
And what we talked about

01:11:53.000 --> 01:11:54.000
in the lecture today

01:11:55.000 --> 01:11:56.000
will be our daily practice,

01:11:57.000 --> 01:11:58.000
our daily work

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:00.000
on reducing self-worth

01:12:01.000 --> 01:12:02.000
and increasing productivity.

01:12:02.000 --> 01:12:03.000
In addition to reducing self-worth

01:12:04.000 --> 01:12:05.000
and increasing the volume of production

01:12:06.000 --> 01:12:07.000
and increasing profits,

01:12:08.000 --> 01:12:09.000
it is very important

01:12:10.000 --> 01:12:11.000
to imagine

01:12:12.000 --> 01:12:13.000
the reserves

01:12:14.000 --> 01:12:15.000
of the enterprises

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:17.000
according to these indicators.

01:12:18.000 --> 01:12:19.000
If the reserve

01:12:20.000 --> 01:12:21.000
of the growth of productivity

01:12:22.000 --> 01:12:23.000
and the reserve

01:12:24.000 --> 01:12:25.000
of the growth of the volume of production

01:12:26.000 --> 01:12:27.000
and the reserve

01:12:28.000 --> 01:12:29.000
of the reduction of the volume

01:12:30.000 --> 01:12:31.000
of production

01:12:32.000 --> 01:12:33.000
and the reserve

01:12:34.000 --> 01:12:35.000
of the reduction of self-worth

01:12:36.000 --> 01:12:37.000
and the reserve

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:39.000
of the increase of the quality

01:12:40.000 --> 01:12:41.000
of production.

01:12:42.000 --> 01:12:43.000
If the reserve exists

01:12:44.000 --> 01:12:45.000
for the achievement of this reserve,

01:12:46.000 --> 01:12:47.000
it is worth fighting,

01:12:48.000 --> 01:12:49.000
it is worth sending forces there.

01:12:50.000 --> 01:12:51.000
The financiers solve this issue

01:12:52.000 --> 01:12:53.000
and this issue is included

01:12:54.000 --> 01:12:55.000
in the program of our lecture today.

01:12:56.000 --> 01:12:57.000
The slide you see now

01:12:58.000 --> 01:12:59.000
shows examples

01:13:00.000 --> 01:13:01.000
of the reserve

01:13:02.000 --> 01:13:03.000
of the growth of productivity.

01:13:04.000 --> 01:13:05.000
It is a reserve of profit.

01:13:06.000 --> 01:13:07.000
Yes, it is.

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:09.000
We have already discussed

01:13:10.000 --> 01:13:11.000
that if we are talking

01:13:12.000 --> 01:13:13.000
about non-elastic goods,

01:13:14.000 --> 01:13:15.000
then it makes sense

01:13:16.000 --> 01:13:17.000
to increase the volume of production

01:13:18.000 --> 01:13:19.000
and at the same time

01:13:20.000 --> 01:13:21.000
to reduce the price.

01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:23.000
If we are talking

01:13:24.000 --> 01:13:25.000
about elastic goods,

01:13:26.000 --> 01:13:27.000
then we should be very careful

01:13:28.000 --> 01:13:29.000
with increasing the volume of production.

01:13:29.000 --> 01:13:30.000
We should look at the possibility

01:13:31.000 --> 01:13:32.000
of increasing the volume of production.

01:13:33.000 --> 01:13:34.000
If we have such an opportunity,

01:13:35.000 --> 01:13:36.000
if we have a limited amount

01:13:37.000 --> 01:13:38.000
of products in our warehouse

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:40.000
and we are told

01:13:41.000 --> 01:13:42.000
that it is easy

01:13:43.000 --> 01:13:44.000
to increase the volume of production

01:13:45.000 --> 01:13:46.000
by 2-10 times,

01:13:47.000 --> 01:13:48.000
then we can consider

01:13:49.000 --> 01:13:50.000
increasing the volume of production

01:13:51.000 --> 01:13:52.000
as a reserve of profit.

01:13:53.000 --> 01:13:54.000
We reduce the price,

01:13:55.000 --> 01:13:56.000
the demand increases sharply

01:13:57.000 --> 01:13:58.000
because our goods are elastic.

01:13:59.000 --> 01:14:00.000
We increase the reserve

01:14:01.000 --> 01:14:02.000
of increasing the volume of production

01:14:03.000 --> 01:14:04.000
and we increase the volume

01:14:05.000 --> 01:14:06.000
of the produced goods in several times.

01:14:07.000 --> 01:14:08.000
Yes, the profit of a unit of production

01:14:09.000 --> 01:14:10.000
decreases,

01:14:11.000 --> 01:14:12.000
but because the volume of production

01:14:13.000 --> 01:14:14.000
increases sharply,

01:14:15.000 --> 01:14:16.000
the product of increasing

01:14:17.000 --> 01:14:18.000
the volume of production

01:14:19.000 --> 01:14:20.000
increases the profit

01:14:21.000 --> 01:14:22.000
of a unit of production.

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:24.000
It is a serious reserve.

01:14:25.000 --> 01:14:26.000
We should take it seriously,

01:14:27.000 --> 01:14:28.000
calculate it taking into account

01:14:29.000 --> 01:14:30.000
whether we can get additional profit

01:14:31.000 --> 01:14:33.000
by increasing the volume of production.

01:14:34.000 --> 01:14:35.000
The second way is reducing

01:14:36.000 --> 01:14:37.000
the cost of production.

01:14:38.000 --> 01:14:39.000
I told you about it today.

01:14:40.000 --> 01:14:41.000
There is a direct way

01:14:42.000 --> 01:14:43.000
to reduce the cost of production.

01:14:44.000 --> 01:14:45.000
There are no alternative options.

01:14:46.000 --> 01:14:47.000
By reducing the cost of production

01:14:48.000 --> 01:14:49.000
we can increase the profit

01:14:50.000 --> 01:14:51.000
because the profit,

01:14:52.000 --> 01:14:53.000
as you remember,

01:14:54.000 --> 01:14:55.000
is the difference between the revenue

01:14:56.000 --> 01:14:57.000
and the cost of production.

01:14:57.000 --> 01:14:58.000
If we reduce the cost of production

01:14:59.000 --> 01:15:00.000
we get more profit.

01:15:01.000 --> 01:15:02.000
You may ask

01:15:03.000 --> 01:15:04.000
why we do not reduce

01:15:05.000 --> 01:15:07.000
the cost of production so sharply.

01:15:08.000 --> 01:15:09.000
Why do we go this way

01:15:10.000 --> 01:15:11.000
in the last place?

01:15:12.000 --> 01:15:13.000
Why do we think about it

01:15:14.000 --> 01:15:15.000
in the last place

01:15:16.000 --> 01:15:18.000
despite the obviousness of this way?

01:15:19.000 --> 01:15:20.000
The answer is simple.

01:15:21.000 --> 01:15:22.000
The fact is that every businessman

01:15:23.000 --> 01:15:24.000
decides

01:15:24.000 --> 01:15:26.000
the task

01:15:27.000 --> 01:15:29.000
that is in front of him.

01:15:30.000 --> 01:15:31.000
To reduce the cost of production

01:15:32.000 --> 01:15:34.000
we should make certain efforts.

01:15:35.000 --> 01:15:36.000
For example,

01:15:37.000 --> 01:15:38.000
we should update the equipment

01:15:39.000 --> 01:15:41.000
and install more advanced equipment.

01:15:42.000 --> 01:15:43.000
Advanced equipment

01:15:44.000 --> 01:15:46.000
means often imported equipment,

01:15:47.000 --> 01:15:49.000
expensive equipment.

01:15:50.000 --> 01:15:51.000
A businessman decides the task.

01:15:52.000 --> 01:15:53.000
If he buys this expensive equipment

01:15:54.000 --> 01:15:56.000
and installs it,

01:15:57.000 --> 01:15:59.000
how much will he save

01:16:00.000 --> 01:16:01.000
on the salary

01:16:02.000 --> 01:16:04.000
of the workers who get money?

01:16:05.000 --> 01:16:06.000
He will save nothing.

01:16:07.000 --> 01:16:08.000
He will save a penny.

01:16:09.000 --> 01:16:10.000
Is it worth buying this equipment

01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:12.000
and increasing the cost of production

01:16:13.000 --> 01:16:14.000
and reducing the cost of production?

01:16:15.000 --> 01:16:16.000
Why?

01:16:17.000 --> 01:16:18.000
What if the purchased equipment

01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:20.000
will lead to a significant reduction

01:16:21.000 --> 01:16:22.000
because the salary is very high

01:16:22.000 --> 01:16:24.000
and the cost of production is very high?

01:16:25.000 --> 01:16:26.000
Then this equipment

01:16:27.000 --> 01:16:28.000
will be bought very quickly.

01:16:29.000 --> 01:16:30.000
Then yes.

01:16:31.000 --> 01:16:32.000
Then it makes sense to buy

01:16:33.000 --> 01:16:35.000
new equipment and reduce the cost of production.

01:16:36.000 --> 01:16:37.000
But until you can pay

01:16:38.000 --> 01:16:40.000
the smallest salary,

01:16:41.000 --> 01:16:43.000
which is simply impossible to pay,

01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:45.000
until you can buy

01:16:46.000 --> 01:16:47.000
new equipment,

01:16:48.000 --> 01:16:50.000
there is no reason.

01:16:50.000 --> 01:16:52.000
There is another important point.

01:16:53.000 --> 01:16:54.000
The thing is that

01:16:55.000 --> 01:16:57.000
buying imported equipment

01:16:58.000 --> 01:17:00.000
and installing it in your own country

01:17:01.000 --> 01:17:03.000
plays an important role

01:17:04.000 --> 01:17:05.000
in the exchange rate

01:17:06.000 --> 01:17:07.000
of national currencies.

01:17:08.000 --> 01:17:10.000
If the exchange rate of national currency

01:17:11.000 --> 01:17:13.000
is low in a country

01:17:14.000 --> 01:17:16.000
that imports equipment,

01:17:17.000 --> 01:17:19.000
then what is available in our country

01:17:20.000 --> 01:17:21.000
will be very expensive.

01:17:22.000 --> 01:17:23.000
But our equipment park

01:17:24.000 --> 01:17:25.000
is not updated 100%.

01:17:26.000 --> 01:17:27.000
Why?

01:17:28.000 --> 01:17:30.000
Because the equipment is expensive for us.

01:17:31.000 --> 01:17:32.000
It is not expensive for them,

01:17:33.000 --> 01:17:34.000
it is available at every factory.

01:17:35.000 --> 01:17:36.000
But it is expensive for us.

01:17:37.000 --> 01:17:38.000
Our exchange rate is low.

01:17:39.000 --> 01:17:40.000
The closer our exchange rate

01:17:41.000 --> 01:17:43.000
will be to a certain parity,

01:17:44.000 --> 01:17:45.000
to its average level,

01:17:46.000 --> 01:17:47.000
the stronger the currency will be.

01:17:47.000 --> 01:17:49.000
The cheaper the import will be.

01:17:50.000 --> 01:17:51.000
And it will be easier

01:17:52.000 --> 01:17:53.000
to buy new equipment

01:17:54.000 --> 01:17:56.000
that we cannot produce in our country.

01:17:57.000 --> 01:17:58.000
And vice versa.

01:17:59.000 --> 01:18:00.000
In a country

01:18:01.000 --> 01:18:02.000
where national currency

01:18:03.000 --> 01:18:04.000
is highly fortified,

01:18:05.000 --> 01:18:06.000
buying imported equipment

01:18:07.000 --> 01:18:08.000
becomes very cheap.

01:18:09.000 --> 01:18:10.000
If in our country

01:18:11.000 --> 01:18:12.000
there were no such problems,

01:18:13.000 --> 01:18:15.000
we would have a very good exchange rate.

01:18:15.000 --> 01:18:16.000
If in our country

01:18:17.000 --> 01:18:18.000
the exchange rate

01:18:19.000 --> 01:18:21.000
was not the same as it is today,

01:18:22.000 --> 01:18:24.000
when we have undervalued currency,

01:18:25.000 --> 01:18:26.000
but it was overvalued,

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:29.000
then all our factories

01:18:30.000 --> 01:18:31.000
and enterprises would have updated

01:18:32.000 --> 01:18:33.000
all their equipment.

01:18:34.000 --> 01:18:35.000
We would say

01:18:36.000 --> 01:18:37.000
that we have no old equipment left.

01:18:38.000 --> 01:18:39.000
We have all the latest equipment.

01:18:40.000 --> 01:18:42.000
Why? Because it is all very cheap abroad.

01:18:43.000 --> 01:18:44.000
It is very cheap.

01:18:45.000 --> 01:18:46.000
You can buy it and update

01:18:47.000 --> 01:18:48.000
all production.

01:18:49.000 --> 01:18:50.000
You see, the exchange rate

01:18:51.000 --> 01:18:52.000
affects the use

01:18:53.000 --> 01:18:54.000
of imported equipment

01:18:55.000 --> 01:18:56.000
in our country.

01:18:57.000 --> 01:18:58.000
If the exchange rate is low,

01:18:59.000 --> 01:19:00.000
imported equipment is not used.

01:19:01.000 --> 01:19:02.000
The same goes for equipment

01:19:03.000 --> 01:19:04.000
that is over 100 years old.

01:19:05.000 --> 01:19:06.000
And it is still in factories,

01:19:07.000 --> 01:19:08.000
the machines produced in the 19th century.

01:19:09.000 --> 01:19:10.000
Until now

01:19:11.000 --> 01:19:12.000
I have been to an aviation factory

01:19:12.000 --> 01:19:13.000
where the press

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:15.000
was produced

01:19:16.000 --> 01:19:17.000
in the 19th century.

01:19:18.000 --> 01:19:19.000
It is a German press.

01:19:20.000 --> 01:19:21.000
It works well,

01:19:22.000 --> 01:19:23.000
but it was produced in the 19th century.

01:19:24.000 --> 01:19:25.000
It is not in museums

01:19:26.000 --> 01:19:27.000
any more.

01:19:28.000 --> 01:19:29.000
It is all over the world.

01:19:30.000 --> 01:19:31.000
But it works in our country.

01:19:32.000 --> 01:19:33.000
Because it is expensive

01:19:34.000 --> 01:19:35.000
to buy a similar press,

01:19:36.000 --> 01:19:37.000
a new, modern one,

01:19:38.000 --> 01:19:39.000
even for an aviation factory.

01:19:39.000 --> 01:19:40.000
It is expensive.

01:19:41.000 --> 01:19:42.000
The next point

01:19:43.000 --> 01:19:44.000
that can increase

01:19:45.000 --> 01:19:46.000
the profit

01:19:47.000 --> 01:19:48.000
is to improve the quality of production.

01:19:49.000 --> 01:19:50.000
The quality of production

01:19:51.000 --> 01:19:52.000
is also a controversial issue.

01:19:53.000 --> 01:19:54.000
The quality of production

01:19:55.000 --> 01:19:56.000
means to produce a product

01:19:57.000 --> 01:19:58.000
that brings more profit

01:19:59.000 --> 01:20:00.000
to the manufacturer,

01:20:01.000 --> 01:20:02.000
that meets the needs

01:20:03.000 --> 01:20:04.000
of the buyers.

01:20:05.000 --> 01:20:06.000
And this is a very important point.

01:20:06.000 --> 01:20:07.000
We do not consider

01:20:08.000 --> 01:20:09.000
the conditions

01:20:10.000 --> 01:20:11.000
when a product is produced

01:20:12.000 --> 01:20:13.000
without a defect,

01:20:14.000 --> 01:20:15.000
and then the same product

01:20:16.000 --> 01:20:17.000
is produced without a defect.

01:20:18.000 --> 01:20:19.000
We have already left

01:20:20.000 --> 01:20:21.000
the times

01:20:22.000 --> 01:20:23.000
when the lion's share

01:20:24.000 --> 01:20:25.000
of defective products

01:20:26.000 --> 01:20:27.000
was produced.

01:20:28.000 --> 01:20:29.000
Today, all the products

01:20:30.000 --> 01:20:31.000
are of a proper quality.

01:20:32.000 --> 01:20:33.000
But

01:20:33.000 --> 01:20:34.000
the proper quality

01:20:35.000 --> 01:20:36.000
can be different.

01:20:37.000 --> 01:20:38.000
There is a high quality level,

01:20:39.000 --> 01:20:40.000
an expensive product

01:20:41.000 --> 01:20:42.000
of a high quality level.

01:20:43.000 --> 01:20:44.000
There is also a quality,

01:20:45.000 --> 01:20:46.000
reliable, good,

01:20:47.000 --> 01:20:48.000
but lower quality level,

01:20:49.000 --> 01:20:50.000
even lower, even lower.

01:20:51.000 --> 01:20:52.000
Each product has its own consumer.

01:20:53.000 --> 01:20:54.000
To improve the quality of the product

01:20:55.000 --> 01:20:56.000
is necessary.

01:20:57.000 --> 01:20:58.000
This is a very important point.

01:20:59.000 --> 01:21:00.000
To avoid such a theorization,

01:21:01.000 --> 01:21:02.000
let's move on

01:21:03.000 --> 01:21:04.000
to the practical language.

01:21:05.000 --> 01:21:06.000
There is AutoVaz,

01:21:07.000 --> 01:21:08.000
which produces Zhiguli.

01:21:09.000 --> 01:21:10.000
There are import factories

01:21:11.000 --> 01:21:12.000
that produce cars.

01:21:13.000 --> 01:21:14.000
The difference between Zhiguli

01:21:15.000 --> 01:21:16.000
and imported cars

01:21:17.000 --> 01:21:19.000
is the difference in the quality of the car.

01:21:20.000 --> 01:21:21.000
To improve the quality of the car

01:21:22.000 --> 01:21:23.000
means to produce our product,

01:21:24.000 --> 01:21:25.000
which meets

01:21:26.000 --> 01:21:27.000
the best imported samples.

01:21:28.000 --> 01:21:29.000
This is what we are talking about

01:21:30.000 --> 01:21:31.000
when we talk about improving the quality.

01:21:31.000 --> 01:21:32.000
A better quality car

01:21:33.000 --> 01:21:35.000
is produced at a higher price,

01:21:36.000 --> 01:21:37.000
and it brings a higher profit

01:21:38.000 --> 01:21:39.000
to its manufacturers.

01:21:40.000 --> 01:21:42.000
The desire to produce a quality car,

01:21:43.000 --> 01:21:44.000
as well as the desire to produce

01:21:45.000 --> 01:21:46.000
a quality product,

01:21:47.000 --> 01:21:48.000
should be present,

01:21:49.000 --> 01:21:50.000
organically present

01:21:51.000 --> 01:21:52.000
in any business.

01:21:53.000 --> 01:21:54.000
Only then will it strive for it

01:21:55.000 --> 01:21:56.000
and try to produce

01:21:57.000 --> 01:21:58.000
a better quality car.

01:21:58.000 --> 01:21:59.000
Unfortunately,

01:22:00.000 --> 01:22:01.000
not all our enterprises

01:22:02.000 --> 01:22:03.000
produce products

01:22:04.000 --> 01:22:05.000
of the world's quality.

01:22:06.000 --> 01:22:07.000
There are different reasons

01:22:08.000 --> 01:22:09.000
for this.

01:22:10.000 --> 01:22:11.000
We will not analyze all the reasons,

01:22:12.000 --> 01:22:13.000
but we will focus on some of them.

01:22:14.000 --> 01:22:15.000
The thing is that

01:22:16.000 --> 01:22:17.000
one of the reasons

01:22:18.000 --> 01:22:19.000
for the two-sided protection

01:22:20.000 --> 01:22:21.000
from the state

01:22:22.000 --> 01:22:23.000
and the manufacturers

01:22:24.000 --> 01:22:25.000
is the lack of

01:22:25.000 --> 01:22:26.000
support from the state.

01:22:27.000 --> 01:22:28.000
On the one hand,

01:22:29.000 --> 01:22:30.000
if we do not support

01:22:31.000 --> 01:22:32.000
the domestic manufacturer,

01:22:33.000 --> 01:22:34.000
we can lose it.

01:22:35.000 --> 01:22:36.000
We lost the AZLK plant.

01:22:37.000 --> 01:22:38.000
The Moskvich car

01:22:39.000 --> 01:22:40.000
was a car

01:22:41.000 --> 01:22:42.000
of the previous period.

01:22:43.000 --> 01:22:44.000
We did not support it,

01:22:45.000 --> 01:22:46.000
we lost it.

01:22:47.000 --> 01:22:48.000
If we can approach

01:22:49.000 --> 01:22:50.000
any business

01:22:51.000 --> 01:22:52.000
without supporting it,

01:22:52.000 --> 01:22:53.000
